Except you're way shorter.

00:19:47.373 --> 00:19:48.977
- Who is this Shoji, anyway?

00:19:49.077 --> 00:19:51.014
And how tall is he?

00:19:54.555 --> 00:19:55.557
- Shoji!

00:19:56.325 --> 00:19:59.999
(footsteps pattering)

00:20:02.538 --> 00:20:03.105
What's wrong?

00:20:03.205 --> 00:20:05.443
Your eyes are red.
- Huh?

00:20:05.544 --> 00:20:07.848
My contacts are bothering me
again.

00:20:07.948 --> 00:20:10.219
- But you don't even
wear contacts.

00:20:10.319 --> 00:20:11.355
- Hmm.

00:20:12.925 --> 00:20:14.227
I think I'm far-sighted.

00:20:14.327 --> 00:20:17.166
The further away something
is, the better I can see it.

00:20:17.267 --> 00:20:20.106
But once it gets close,
I lose sight of it.

00:20:22.878 --> 00:20:24.447
- Everyone's like that.

00:20:31.128 --> 00:20:32.463
- Come on, we'd better hold
hands,

00:20:32.565 --> 00:20:35.604
so we don't end up losing
each other in the crowd, okay?

00:20:35.704 --> 00:20:38.275
Especially 'cause you're so
tiny.

00:20:38.375 --> 00:20:41.415
(Sachiko giggling)

00:20:43.920 --> 00:20:45.924
- [Nana O.] Hey, Hachi.

00:20:46.024 --> 00:20:48.697
They say you don't realize
how much you care for someone

00:20:48.797 --> 00:20:50.499
until after they're gone.

00:20:51.569 --> 00:20:53.405
But I think it's when
you come face-to-face

00:20:53.506 --> 00:20:54.675
with that person once more,

00:20:54.775 --> 00:20:57.715
that you truly recognize
your feelings for them.

00:20:58.817 --> 00:21:02.257
If I saw everyone
again right now,

00:21:02.357 --> 00:21:03.860
I know that I'd depend on them

00:21:03.960 --> 00:21:06.164
just as much as I did back then.

00:21:08.235 --> 00:21:09.705
